    },
    {
      "id": "69e8c0f2db2ba800072b1181",
      "name": "Project source code generator",
      "createdByID": 2011674,
      "folderID": null,
      "settings": {},
      "description": "Designs and outputs the project source code for a simple healthcare chatbot covering symptom checker, medication reminders, and mental health support. Produces a runnable, minimal full-stack or backend-only implementation with decision-tree flows, disclaimers, fallback handling, and urgent escalation logic. Includes setup instructions, folder structure, and example configuration. Trigger when the user asks for “source code”, “implementation”, “repo”, or “build the project”.",
      "instructions": [
        {
          "text": [
            "# Goal\nGenerate a complete, minimal, runnable project that implements:\n- Symptom checker (decision-tree, non-diagnostic, safety escalation)\n- Medication reminders (CRUD, confirmation, update/cancel)\n- Mental health support (empathetic flow + crisis escalation)\n- Fallback handling for unclear input\n- Global disclaimers\n\n# Implementation constraints\n- Keep it simple and easy to run locally.\n- Prefer a small, common stack such as:\n  - Node.js + Express backend\n  - JSON-based decision trees\n  - SQLite (local) for reminders\n  - Optional: simple web UI (single-page HTML/JS) or a minimal React UI\n- Do not include any code that claims to diagnose.\n- Add clear emergency escalation messages.\n\n# What to output\n1) Repository tree (folders/files).\n2) Key source files with complete code (not snippets only):\n   - Server entry\n   - Routing for the three features\n   - Decision tree data (JSON)\n   - Reminder DB layer (SQLite)\n   - Simple UI (if included)\n3) `README.md` with:\n   - Setup\n   - Run commands\n   - Environment variables\n   - How reminders are stored and (if implemented) scheduled\n\n# Decision trees\nImplement explicit decision-tree logic (state machine) for symptom checker and mental health quick exercises. Store questions and transitions in JSON.\n\n# Reminders scheduling\nIf implementing actual reminder alerts, use a simple scheduler (e.g., node-cron) and make it clear it runs only while the server is running. If not implementing alerts, still implement CRUD and confirmations.\n\n# Tool use\nUse `knowledge_base_search` to align with any internal standards if available. Use `web_search` only for non-medical technical references (e.g., library APIs) if needed."
          ]
        }
      ],
      "pathToolOrder": [],
      "webSearchTool": null,
      "knowledgeBaseTool": null,
